</form><html xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:math="java.lang.Math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions" xmlns:xdt="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-datatypes" xmlns:caml="http://lc.ca.gov/legalservices/schemas/caml.1#" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><title>AJR24:v99#DOCUMENT</title><meta name="dc:identifier" content="AJR24"/><meta name="dc:title" content="AJR &#xA;              24-&#xA;                INTRODUCED&#xA;              "/><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8"/></head><body><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Start</h2></span><div id="bill_all" align="justify"><div id="about"><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td align="center"/></tr></tbody></table></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><font size="3" style="FONT-FAMILY: MinionPC, Arial Unicode MS">
                    CALIFORNIA LEGISLATURE—
                    2025–2026 REGULAR SESSION</font></div><br clear="all"/><span id="bill_house_num"><div style="float: left; width:50%; font-weight: bold; "><span style="text-transform: uppercase; text-align:left;width:50%;"><b>
                Assembly Joint Resolution
              </b></span></div><div style="float:right; width:50%; text-align:right;"><span style="text-transform: uppercase;"><b>No. 24</b></span></div></span><hr/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td id="bill_authors" align="center"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Introduced by Assembly Members Wallis, Castillo, Davies, Jeff Gonzalez, and Hoover<br/></span></td></tr><tr><td id="bill_intro_date" align="center" class="textcenter"><br/>January 08, 2026</td></tr></tbody></table></div><hr/><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> Relative to enhanced premium tax credits. </span></div><br clear="all"/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">AJR 24, as introduced, Wallis.
                          Health care coverage: enhanced premium tax credits: health savings accounts.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This measure would call upon Congress to reauthorize the enhanced premium tax credits and would urge Congress to continue exploring the concept of bolstering health savings accounts, as specified. </div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><span class="Resolution" title="source: /caml:MeasureDoc/caml:Resolution&#xA;    "><span class="Whereas" id="id_0D2A6621-3A06-4A1E-98F0-DE9CB5956F82"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Since the passage of the Affordable Care Act (ACA), health care affordability has become a serious concern in most American households, with premiums on the individual market increasing by up to approximately 150 percent; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_FAF461F8-3D2E-4E99-B11B-52FEE6C1BD20"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, These cost increases cannot be attributed to a single source, but rather are the result of numerous policy changes which have driven up the cost of care; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_FFB0FBB2-198C-4D70-B8B4-A8ECAD8D333B"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, In an effort to mitigate premium increases for low-income families, the ACA authorized premium tax credits, later expanded into the enhanced premium tax credits (ePTCs) in the American Rescue Plan Act of 2021, which offer low-income families financial assistance when purchasing health care coverage, reducing premiums by up to 75 percent; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_2749CC5F-F93D-43CF-8839-4EDFA5733FDC"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The ePTCs are set to expire at the end of 2025, resulting in a detrimental impact for all beneficiaries, with premiums anticipated to increase by as much as 100 percent; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_3AE59960-C675-44A3-9AC5-066CD7B2F9E0"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, In 2003, President George W. Bush signed the Medicare Prescription Drug, Improvement, and Modernization Act, which created health savings accounts (HSAs), allowing persons to make tax-free contributions and withdrawals to cover the costs of certain medical expenses; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_EF2362F8-A3BF-46E5-A510-23CB6B40B11B"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, HSAs, in conjunction with ePTCs, have provided American families with the opportunity to proactively save for medical expenses; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_F7B1F776-A6FB-4D16-8623-8DD007304DE7"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Recent Congressional deliberations have centered around extending the ePTCs, as well as issuing federal contributions to HSAs, and collectively these efforts provide low-income persons with the overall greatest premium assistance and should be included within any premium assistance legislative proposal; now, therefore, be it</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_AF9C81C2-8732-4198-980C-F27890C6749F"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved by the Assembly and the Senate of the State of California, jointly, That the Legislature calls upon Congress to reauthorize the ePTCs; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_8CE8E9B7-5E8C-4DA7-8C71-856D1687D640"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Legislature urges Congress to continue exploring the concept of bolstering the HSAs of people making up to 700 percent of the federal poverty line with a high-deductible plan; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_33C2F7FF-5ABA-4202-931D-C46AF1FD57B3"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Chief Clerk of the Assembly transmit copies of this resolution to the President and Vice President of the United States, to the Speaker of the United States House of Representatives, to the Majority Leader of the United States Senate, to each Senator and Representative from California in the Congress of the United States, and to the author for appropriate distribution.</div></span></span></div></body></html>
